      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elasto-plastic constitutive model with isotropic hardening is appropriate for Ti-6Al-4V screw material under quasi-static loading; model form justified by literature and prior validation studies.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening (BISO) constitutive model used for Ti-6Al-4V. Model form is consistent with published FDA and academic validation studies for pedicle screw constructs under quasi-static bending. Geometric nonlinearity enabled to capture large-displacement effects at 40 mm displacement target."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties (E, yield stress, tangent modulus) sourced from coupon tensile tests on the same material lot; geometric dimensions from CMM measurements of production screws.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus, yield strength, and tangent modulus obtained from uniaxial tensile coupon tests (n=5) on Ti-6Al-4V from the same material lot as the tested constructs. Screw and rod geometry verified by coordinate measuring machine (CMM) to within ±0.01 mm of nominal CAD dimensions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
