      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions match ASTM F1717 protocol including loading rate, fixture geometry, and environmental conditions; multiple test conditions evaluated.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed strictly per ASTM F1717 at a single loading rate (5 mm/min) and ambient temperature. Only one test condition evaluated; the required level of 2 is not achieved due to absence of additional loading rate or temperature conditions. This shortfall is documented and accepted given the standardized nature of the ASTM protocol and the medium model risk level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA model inputs (geometry, material properties, boundary conditions) demonstrably equivalent to experimental test conditions; traceability documented.",
      "rationale": "One-to-one traceability established between FEA inputs and experimental measurements: geometry from CMM data, material properties from coupon tests on same lot, boundary conditions from F1717 fixture drawings. Equivalency matrix completed and reviewed."
    },
    {
