      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison using E/uval metric; E/uval < 1.96 and QoI difference < 10% for all three quantities of interest.",
      "rationale": "E/uval computed for stiffness (1.41), yield force (0.93), and force at 40 mm (0.87). All values below 1.96 threshold. QoI differences are 7.3%, 4.1%, and 2.9% respectively, all within the 10% bound. Quantitative output comparison criterion fully satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) are directly relevant to the clinical failure mode of interest (screw-rod construct fatigue and fracture under physiological loading).",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing with the spine; yield force indicates onset of permanent deformation; force at 40 mm displacement characterizes post-yield behavior relevant to fracture risk. All three QoIs are established in ASTM F1717 as the standard measures for spinal implant construct performance."
    },
